11 An Act relating to higher education; amending 70 O.S.
2021, Section 2120, as amended by Section 3, Chapter
12 18, O.S.L. 2022 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 2120),
which relates to protected expressive activities on
13 campus; permitting public institutions of higher
education to charge security fees to students and
14 student organization as part of an application for
expressive activities; prohibiting public
15 institutions of higher education from charging
security fees based on the content of the student's
16 or student organization's expression, the content of
the student's or student organization's invited
17 guest's expression, or the anticipated reaction to
the student's, student organization's, or invited
18 guest's expression; requiring any required security
fee be based on content- and viewpoint-neutral
19 criteria; directing public institutions of higher
education to publish criteria on its website;
20 requiring public institutions of higher education to
provide notice to a student or student organization
21 prior to the expressive activity an explanation of
the security fee to be charged; providing an
22 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
